claim.claim-text:
1. A circuit for clamping a word line voltage comprising: 
a reference voltage generating means for generating a reference voltage depending on a first signal; 
a bootstrap circuit for generating a pumping voltage of a higher potential than a target voltage depending on said first and second signals to an output terminal; 
a control signal generating means for generating said first and second control signals depending on said first˜third signals; 
a clamping control means for falling said the pumping voltage depending said first and second control signals to generate a compare voltage; 
a comparator for comparing said reference voltage and said compare voltage to generate a third signal; and 
a discharging means for discharging the potential of said output terminal depending on said third signal to fall said pumping voltage to a target voltage.

3. The circuit for clamping a word line voltage according to claim 1, wherein said control signal generating means includes: 
a first NAND gate for receiving said first and second signals as an input; 
a first inverter for inverting an output signal of said first NAND gate; 
a first delay means for delaying the output signal of said first inverter; 
a first NOR gate for receiving the output signals of said first inverter and said first delay means; 
a second NAND gate for receiving said first and third signals as an input; 
a second inverter for inverting the output signal of said second NAND gate; 
a second delay means for delaying the output signal of said second inverter; 
a second NOR gate for receiving the output signals of said second inverter and said second delay means; 
a third NAND gate for receiving the output signals of said first and second NOR gates to generate said first control signal; and 
a third inverter for inverting the output signal of said third NAND gate to generate said fourth control signal.

5. The circuit for clamping a word line voltage according to claim 4, wherein said sub clamping control means includes: 
a first transistor drain and gate terminals of which are connected to said output terminal, for falling said pumping voltage to generate said first voltage; 
a second transistor drain and gate terminals of which are connected to said source terminal of said first transistor, for falling said first voltage to generate said second voltage; 
a third transistor drain and gate terminals of which are connected to said source terminal of said second transistor, for falling said second voltage to generate said third voltage; 
a fourth transistor connected between said third transistor and said ground terminal; 
a first transfer for connecting said drain and gate terminal of said fourth transistor depending on said first and second control signals; and 
a fifth transistor for connecting a gate terminal of said fourth transistor and said ground terminal.

8. The circuit for clamping a word line voltage according to claim 4, wherein said main clamping control means includes: 
sixth˜eighth transistors serially connected to said output terminal and to each of triple p-wells of which is applied said first˜third voltages, wherein a gate terminal and a triple n-well of said sixth˜eighth transistors are connected to its drain terminals; 
a ninth transistor connected between said eighth transistor and said ground terminal and to triple n-well of which is applied the power supply voltage, wherein a triple p-well of said ninth transistor is connected to said ground terminal; 
a second transfer gate connecting said drain and gate terminals of said ninth transistor depending on said first and second control signals, for transferring the fallen voltage by said sixth˜eighth transistor to said output terminal as a compare voltage; and 
a tenth transistor for connecting said gate terminal of said ninth transistor and said ground terminal depending on said second control signal.

11. A circuit for clamping a word line voltage comprising: 
a reference voltage generating means for generating a reference voltage depending on a first signal; 
a bootstrap circuit for generating the potential of a pumping voltage higher than that of a target voltage, depending on said first signal and a second signal to an output terminal; 
a control signal generating means for generating first and second control signals, depending on said first˜third signals; 
a clamping control means including a sub-clamping control means and a main clamping control means, said sub-clamping control means falling said pumping voltage to generate first˜third voltages depending on said first and second control signals and said main clamping control means falling said pumping voltage to generate a compare voltage depending on said first and second control signals, wherein the threshold voltage of a transistor for falling the voltage to a triple p-well of which is applied said first˜third voltages to adjust said compare voltage; 
a comparator for comparing said reference voltage and said compare voltage to generate a third signal; and 
a discharging means for discharging the potential of said output terminal depending on said third signal to fall said pumping voltage to a target voltage.

13. The circuit for clamping a word line voltage according to claim 11, wherein said control signal generating means includes: 
a first NAND gate for receiving said first and second signals as an input; 
a first inverter for inverting the output signal of said first NAND gate; 
a first delay means for delaying the output signal of said first inverter; 
a first NOR gate for receiving the output signals of said first inverter and said first delay means as an input; 
a second NAND gate for receiving said first and third signals; 
a second inverter for inverting the output signal of said second NAND gate; 
a second delay means for delaying the output signal of said second inverter; 
a second NOR gate for receiving the output signals of said second inverter and said second delay means as an input; 
a third NAND gate for receiving the output signal of said first and second NOR gates as an input to generate said first control signal; and 
a third inverter for inverting the output signal of said third NAND gate to generate said fourth control signal.

14. The circuit for clamping a word line voltage according to claim 11, wherein said sub clamping control means includes: 
a first transistor a drain and a gate terminal of which are connected to said output terminal, for falling said pumping voltage to generate said first voltage; 
a second transistor the drain and the gate terminal of which are connected to a source terminal of said first transistor, for falling said first transistor to generate said second voltage 
a third transistor a drain and a gate terminal of which are connected to a source terminal of said second transistor, for falling said second voltage to generate said third voltage; 
a fourth transistor connected between said third transistor and the ground terminal; 
a first transfer gate for connecting the drain and gate terminal of said fourth transistor depending on said first and second control signals; and 
a fifth transistor for connecting the gate terminal of said fourth transistor and the ground terminal.

17. The circuit for clamping a word line voltage according to claim 11, wherein said main clamping control means includes: 
sixth˜eighth transistors serially connected to said output terminal, gate terminals and triple n-wells of which are connected to its drain terminals and to each of triple p-wells of which are supplied with said first˜third voltages to fall said pumping voltage; 
a ninth transistor connected between said eighth transistor and said ground terminal, to a triple n-well of which is applied the power supply voltage and a triple p-well of which is connected to said ground terminal; 
a second transfer gate for connecting the drain and gate terminals of said ninth transistor depending on said first and second control signals, for transferring the voltage fallen by said sixth˜eighth transistors to said output terminal as a compare voltage; and 
a tenth transistor for connecting the gate terminal of said ninth transistor and said ground terminal depending on said second control signal.
